wgputoy WASM render() match: add SurfaceError::Other arm

Upstream (compute-toys/wgpu-compute-toy @ 60d0bec4bd91…) has two
`match err { … }` blocks in src/lib.rs:
- the WASM render()        at line ~148 → missing SurfaceError::Other
- the non-WASM render_async() at line ~184 → already has it

wgpu 24.0.x adds the Other variant unconditionally → the WASM build
fails with E0004 ("pattern `SurfaceError::Other` not covered").

This patch is generated via `git diff -U3` so it carries surrounding
context — `patch -p1` / `git apply --check` will refuse to apply (and
fail LOUDLY) if upstream changes either match block, instead of
silently relocating like a bare sed.

Tracked: github.com/utensil/forest/issues/54 item 1.
To drop: upstream PR adding the missing arm + bump prep_wasm hash in
build.sh + pins.hash in flake.nix.

